{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Fluid Sim 2D",
  "description": "Density-displacement particle compute fluid simulation — decomposed from `FluidSimulationGenerator` + `FluidSimCore` into the curated primitive library. Per-frame pipeline: array-feedback emits last frame's particle positions; scatter splats them additively (toroidal wrap, scaled_energy from splat_size / particles), resolve lifts the u32 accumulator into an rgba16float density texture; downsample 2x + separable Gaussian blur produces blur_density; fluid_gradient_rotate computes a vec2 force field (toroidal central-difference gradient scaled by slope_strength, rotated by rotation_angle, density_area_scale baked in via reference_area=1920×1080); another separable blur produces field_blurred; fluid_simulate consumes (in particles, blurred field, blurred density) and mutates positions in-place (aliased in/out). The display path taps the full-res density before downsample and runs the legacy extended-Reinhard tone curve (intensity * area_scale * 3.0, contrast user-controlled) followed by an affine_transform UV zoom.\n\nClip-trigger envelope: `trigger_gate` gates raw trigger_count by `clip_trigger > 0.5`; `envelope_decay` (rate 12.0) produces a one-shot 0→1 envelope per gated edge. Five modes are dispatched via mux:\n- mode 0 (noise burst): noise_amplitude *= 1 + 9*env\n- mode 1 (rotation flip): rotation_angle += π*env\n- mode 2 (slope sign-flip): slope_strength *= 1 - 2*env\n- mode 3 (re-seed): trigger_gate(clip_trigger AND mode==3) → fluid_seed.trigger, fires a fresh pattern (pattern=0 default — see known delta)\n- mode 4 (inject point): `inject_burst` runs a 0.5s state machine producing (active, point_x, point_y, phase) that drives fluid_simulate's inject port-shadows\n\nKnown parity deltas vs legacy:\n(1) gaussian_blur uses node.gaussian_blur's fixed 17-tap kernel + `step` scaled from outer `blur_radius` slider — legacy uses a dynamic sigma `max(radius/3, 1.0)` with bilinear tap-pair. Density softness will visibly differ; outer `blur_radius` slider has a roughly proportional effect.\n(2) display tone curve composes reinhard_tone_map (intensity * extended Reinhard) + affine_transform (uv_scale) — close to legacy but not bit-exact (the fused legacy shader has different UV recenter math).\n(3) clip-trigger mode 3 re-seed always uses pattern 0 — legacy cycles patterns 0..6 via ClipTriggerCycle. Pattern cycling requires graph-level modulo plumbing (math primitives lack modulo); deferred.\n(4) clip-trigger active_mode is read live from the slider — legacy holds the mode that was active when the trigger fired. Performer-affecting only if mode is changed mid-envelope-decay (~0.08s window); acceptable for live use.\n(5) clip-trigger mode 3 re-seed will produce a ~16ms GPU pipeline hitch on each fire — legacy skips the full pipeline on seed frames to avoid this; the graph runtime lacks per-frame sub-graph gating. Hitch is intrinsic until that runtime feature lands.",
